is\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.488261317011693e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympic rings\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 343}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 347, \"to\": 363}, {\"ngram\": \"a symbol\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 382}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Games\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 406}, {\"ngram\": \"Source\", \"from\": 407, \"to\": 413}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic rings\", \"from\": 484, \"to\": 501}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 515, \"to\": 531}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The five interlocking rings - which have represented the Olympic Games for more than a century - were installed on the Eiffel Tower before the 2024 Paris Olympics opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 547, \"to\": 727, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The five interlocking rings\", \"from\": 547, \"to\": 574}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 600, \"to\": 617}, {\"ngram\": \"more than a century\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 641}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 678}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Olympics opening ceremony\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 726}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The giant logo on the famous tower has been a symbol of the Paris Olympics and Paralympics and a popular backdrop for selfies by visitors to Paris.\", \"from\": 729, \"to\": 876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 870, \"end\": 875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.488261317011693e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The giant logo\", \"from\": 729, \"to\": 743}, {\"ngram\": \"the famous tower\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 763}, {\"ngram\": \"a symbol\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 781}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 803}, {\"ngram\": \"Paralympics\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 819}, {\"ngram\": \"a popular backdrop\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 842}, {\"ngram\": \"selfies\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 854}, {\"ngram\": \"visitors\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 866}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rings were due be taken down after the Paralympics' closing ceremony on 8 September.\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 966, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The rings\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 887}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paralympics' closing ceremony\", \"from\": 917, \"to\": 950}, {\"ngram\": \"8 September\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 965}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But mayor Anne Hidalgo said in an interview over the weekend she intends to keep them on the tower.\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 1066, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 977, \"end\": 989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an interview\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1010}, {\"ngram\": \"the weekend\", \"from\": 1016, \"to\": 1027}, {\"ngram\": \"the tower\", \"from\": 1056, \"to\": 1065}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The plan to keep the rings has triggered heated debate among Parisians and has been criticised by the descendants of the tower's namesake, engineer Gustave Eiffel.\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1231, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1216, \"end\": 1230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gustave Eiffel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gustave_Eiffel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The plan\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1076}, {\"ngram\": \"the rings\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1094}, {\"ngram\": \"heated debate\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1122}, {\"ngram\": \"Parisians\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1138}, {\"ngram\": \"the descendants\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1181}, {\"ngram\": \"the tower's namesake\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1205}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Association of Gustave Eiffel's Descendants said in a statement they were \\\"delighted\\\" to see the Eiffel Tower bear the rings during the 2024 Games.\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Association\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1248}, {\"ngram\": \"Gustave Eiffel's Descendants\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1280}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1300}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1346}, {\"ngram\": \"the rings\", \"from\": 1352, \"to\": 1361}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Games\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1383}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, they continued: \\\"It does not seem appropriate to us that the Eiffel Tower, which has become the symbol of Paris and the whole of France since its construction 135 years ago, has the symbol of an outside organisation added to it in a permanent way, whatever its prestige.\\\"\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1501, \"end\": 1506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.488261317011693e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1524, \"end\": 1530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999832657523, \"rank\": 7.299046417959732e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1446}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1468}, {\"ngram\": \"the symbol\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1497}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1520}, {\"ngram\": \"its construction\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1553}, {\"ngram\": \"the symbol\", \"from\": 1573, \"to\": 1583}, {\"ngram\": \"an outside organisation\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1610}, {\"ngram\": \"a permanent way\", \"from\": 1626, \"to\": 1641}, {\"ngram\": \"its prestige\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1664}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The association's chairman Olivier Berthelot-Eiffel, a great-great-grandson of Eiffel, who designed and built the tower, told the Agence France-Presse that the family did not see any problem with the rings staying longer than the Paralympic Games, which wrap up on 8 September.\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1798, \"end\": 1818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Agence France-Presse\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The association's chairman\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1694}, {\"ngram\": \"Olivier Berthelot-Eiffel\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1719}, {\"ngram\": \"a great-great-grandson\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1743}, {\"ngram\": \"Eiffel\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1753}, {\"ngram\": \"the tower\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1787}, {\"ngram\": \"the family\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1834}, {\"ngram\": \"any problem\", \"from\": 1847, \"to\": 1858}, {\"ngram\": \"the rings\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1873}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paralympic Games\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 1914}, {\"ngram\": \"8 September\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1944}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But the Eiffel Tower should not become an advertising outpost.\", \"from\": 1947, \"to\": 2010, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1952, \"to\": 1968}, {\"ngram\": \"an advertising outpost\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2009}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anne Hidalgo should have said that she wanted to keep the Olympic rings, not that she had decided it, and then discussed the idea with the Paris council and relevant individuals,\\\" he explained.\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2011, \"end\": 2023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 2150, \"end\": 2155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.488261317011693e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic rings\", \"from\": 2065, \"to\": 2082}, {\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2140}, {\"ngram\": \"relevant individuals\", \"from\": 2168, \"to\": 2188}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's culture minister Rachida Dati also cast doubt over the idea, saying the mayor would need to follow procedures protecting historic buildings.\", \"from\": 2206, \"to\": 2355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2206, \"end\": 2212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999832657523, \"rank\": 7.299046417959732e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2232, \"end\": 2244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rachida Dati\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"doubt\", \"from\": 2255, \"to\": 2260}, {\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2274}, {\"ngram\": \"the mayor\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2292}, {\"ngram\": \"procedures\", \"from\": 2314, \"to\": 2324}, {\"ngram\": \"historic buildings\", \"from\": 2336, \"to\": 2354}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Eiffel Tower is a protected monument, the work of an immense engineer and designer,\\\" Dati said in a statement.\", \"from\": 2357, \"to\": 2472, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 2358, \"to\": 2374}, {\"ngram\": \"a protected monument\", \"from\": 2378, \"to\": 2398}, {\"ngram\": \"the work\", \"from\": 2400, \"to\": 2408}, {\"ngram\": \"an immense engineer\", \"from\": 2412, \"to\": 2431}, {\"ngram\": \"designer\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2444}, {\"ngram\": \"Dati\", \"from\": 2447, \"to\": 2451}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 2460, \"to\": 2471}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A petition on Change.org against keeping the Olympic rings on the Eiffel Tower had been signed by more than 27,000 people on Tuesday morning, with some critics pointing out the tower is part of a UNESCO World Heritage site.\", \"from\": 2474, \"to\": 2697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2488, \"end\": 2498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Change.org\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Change.org\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Change.org\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Change.org\"}, {\"begin\": 2670, \"end\": 2676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNESCO\", \"score\": 0.999933190995228, \"rank\": 6.681346708911615e-05, \"text\": \"UNESCO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNESCO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNESCO\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A petition\", \"from\": 2474, \"to\": 2484}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic rings\", \"from\": 2515, \"to\": 2532},